text: Btw  this is a wheel dyno chart for Honda shuttle hybrid
May I know the TCF figure for this Dyno chart?😊
Hmm tbh  I also donno how to see. I just see the number at the peak and how the tuner explain to me that's all
especially if you're looking at power figures
if not the entire chart you can don't look  just the shape of the graph  because the numbers don't matter
Yeah..from the chart..can't see much details
that's why people say go tune NA car with nothing suddenly +50hp
To go up 70kg plus nm torque..abit..erm...haha
Bhp number not that important to me..torque figure does😁
198 to 272? Super good return😁
any simple theory on how they increase the torque for NA?
Tht is engine + battery at full charge. If battery flat  the torque not so high
Most tuner will play with your AFR. When you have more fuel combusting  it will affect the torque slightly. But don't hope for very high increase in figures if the engine is stock.
Of course if your car is pumping more fuel to combust  your FC will cui. So if want fuel efficiency  you won't high much power. It's like a balancing beam.
From 198 to 272 in terms of nm ...is extremely nice 😁
Usually AFR  throttle response  ignition timing and lamda
The chat 198nm is pure engine power  battery at flat. 270nm is engine + battery with full charge.
Erm..abit cheem..how the batt from flat to full charge in that short period sir
So after power run at full charge  battery will flat. The tuner will just let the car rest and charge up the battery before doing another power run
ah icic ok thanks! air coming in is the limit liao
Power....the batt discharge so fast? One run and flat liao on Dyno?
Different intake set up also affect a car performance. That why you always see ppl comparing between open pod and closed pod intake.
Hybrid is like tht de. The full power to wheels will drain the battery fast.
maybe like F1 can change ah. change to HotLap settings drain the batt
Sadly we don't have the technology like F1 cars. If not charging will be damn fast.
Will trickle down one day to consumer cars😁
Ok  time for me to get back to work. Chat again soon :)
